{
  "stem": "812.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "But for some reason, they didn't want to take the responsibility.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "But through my Aunt Rosie, my father's sister who lived with my mother, we-- my Aunt Rosie's mother-in-law, [?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "Oma ?] Wolf, came to visit one day.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "And when she heard that we were looking, my mother was looking for an affidavit, she said, not to worry.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "Her son would supply the affidavit.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "And this is a person who we had never met, and he lived in Malden, Massachusetts.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "His name was Arnold Wolf.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "And sure enough, within a few weeks time we had the affidavit.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "And with it, of course, he needed to vouch for us, that we wouldn't be a burden to the government here, and $600 had to be supplied or given to-- by him and given to us or put in a bank for us to use in case we needed it.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "Everything was in order, and we left Holland in April of '48 aboard the and the Holland America line.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "And it was really a wonderful trip, and we arrived in Hoboken on April 23, 1948.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] April 23 is a very memorable day in my-- in our lives.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "It was on April 23, exactly April 23, 1945, that we were liberated by the Russians.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "It was April 23, 1948 that we arrived in this wonderful country of America.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "And it was also April 23, 1979 that I gave my first talk [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] on my experiences in the camps as a child.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "And I know that arriving-- before we arrived in-- in the United States aboard, we were told the night before that if we wanted to see the Statue of Liberty the next morning that we should be on board deck early, early in the morning.",
      "word_count": 45
    }
  ],
